If the opening day of Wimbledon was dramatic, day two very much matched it as former champions Rafael Nadal and Serena Williams were both put through the mill. Nadal came through his match in four sets against Francisco Cerúndolo, but for Williams, her long-awaited return ended in sadness. After an epic late-night match on Centre Court, she bowed out to French player Harmony Tan following a final set tie-break.  Following the Serbian will be US Open champion Raducanu, looking to build on her frist-round win over Alison Van Uytvanck. The tenth seed faces French player Caroline Garcia, who reached the last-16 at SW19 back in 2017. Then it will be the turn of Murray, with British fans on edge with every match he plays given the prospect of him imminently retiring. His hopes of a fairytale run this year will depend on how he fares against America's John Isner. And in another treat for home fans, Heather Watson will look to progress again when she plays Qiang Wang on Court 2. Express Sport runs through the full Wimbledon order of play on Day Two. Centre Court (from 1:30pm) Novak Djokovic (1) v Thanasi Kokkinakis Caroline Garcia v Emma Raducanu (10) Andy Murray v John Isner (20) JUST IN: Nick Kyrgios clarifies 'racism' comments after Wimbledon outburst in Paul Jubb clash Court 1 (from 1pm) DON'T MISS:Nick Kyrgios points to Rafael Nadal backlash after Andy Murray Wimbledon trickRafael Nadal officially gets Calendar Slam bid underway in testing Wimbledon winCoco Gauff weighs in on Wimbledon Covid crisis and lifts lid on feeling inside locker room Court 7 Yifan Xu/Zhaoxuan Yang (9) v Lucia Bronzetti/Julia Lohoff Shuko Aoyama/Hao-Ching Chan (8) v Xiyu Wang/Qinwen Zheng Nicolas Mahut/Edouard Roger-Vasselin (12) v Francisco Cerundolo/Tomas Martin Etcheverry Court 8 Santiago Gonzalez/Andres Molteni (13) v Julian Cash/Henry Patten Jasmine Paolini/Martina Trevisan v Naiktha Bains/Maia Lumsden Clara Burel/Chloe Paquet v Xinyun Han/Lin Zhu Mackenzie McDonald/Botic van de Zandschulp 